d\", \"search\", \"erase\", \"erase\", \"search\"]\n[[], [1], [2], [3], [0], [4], [1], [0], [1], [1]]\nOutput\n[null, null, null, null, false, null, true, false, true, false]\n\nExplanation\nSkiplist skiplist = new Skiplist();\nskiplist.add(1);\nskiplist.add(2);\nskiplist.add(3);\nskiplist.search(0); // return False\nskiplist.add(4);\nskiplist.search(1); // return True\nskiplist.erase(0);  // return False, 0 is not in skiplist.\nskiplist.erase(1);  // return True\nskiplist.search(1); // return False, 1 has already been erased.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= num, target <= 2 * 10⁴`\n\n- At most `5 * 10⁴` calls will be made to `search`, `add`, and `erase`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/design-skiplist/","problemName":"Design Skiplist","problemNumber":1206,"problemSlug":"design-skiplist","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1206,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Hash Table"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given an array of integers `arr`, return `true` *if the number of occurrences of each value in the array is **unique** or *`false`* otherwise*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: arr = [1,2,2,1,1,3]\nOutput: true\nExplanation: The value 1 has 3 occurrences, 2 has 2 and 3 has 1. No two values have the same number of occurrences.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: arr = [1,2]\nOutput: false","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: arr = [-3,0,1,-3,1,1,1,-3,10,0]\nOutput: true","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= arr.length <= 1000`\n\n- `-1000 <= arr[i] <= 1000`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Hash Table"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given an array of integers `arr`, return `true` *if the number of occurrences of each value in th